title: For Sale/Trade:  Vzor 50 cal (32ACP) also known as vz.50 or Cz-50 Government Pistol from the 1940's Works Great
postcontent:
The small, pocket-sized Vz.50 was developed during late 1940s for police use and it was chambered for the marginally powerful 7.65x17 Browning ammunition. Apparently influenced by the Walther PP in design, the Vz.50 had several differences in safety and disassembly. In the early 1970s the basic design went through minor face-lift, and the "new" design received the designation of Vz.70. Many Vz.50 pistols were refurbished to Vz.70 standard, with different finish, grip panels and a slightly different safety lever. New Vz.70 pistols were also manufactured between 1970 and 1983. After the replacement in service of the older Vz.50 and Vz.70 by more modern 9mm Vz.82 pistol, most were sold as surplus, as Cz-50 and Cz-70, respectively.

The Vz.50 (commercially sold as Cz-50) is a compact pistol of all-steel construction, firing the relatively weak 7.65mm ammunition. It has a simple blowback action with a fixed barrel. The trigger is double-action, with an exposed hammer and a frame-mounted decocking safety lever. The sights are fixed. Magazines are single stack. The magazine release button is located relatively high on the left side of the frame, behind the trigger. Vz.70 (Cz-70) pistols are similar, with minor differences in the finish, shape of the safety lever and grips. Manual safety is a lever at left side of the frame, behind the trigger guard. To set on safe: pull the lever down; if the hammer was cocked, it will be automatically brought down to rest. To disengage safety: push the lever up; a red dot will appear on the frame. (info from world.guns.ru, not my words)

WILL TRADE FOR 38 SPECIAL OR MANY OTHER 380s or 38 revolvers
Always looking to add to the collection so any trade may be possible

title: For Sale/Trade:  New/Unfired M-4 Type AR-15
postcontent:
For sale is a new and unfired AR-15. Upper is Doublestar Arms (DSA), lower is API (Aero-Precision, whom used to manufacture parts for Armalite before going into their own business. I know that this technically makes this a 'franken-AR', so if you're looking for a rifle to hang on a display, this isn't your rifle. If you're looking for a rifle that is durable, reliable, and which can put years worth of rounds downrange, this *is* your rifle. 

Barrel is 1:9 twist, optomized for 55 gr (approximately) rounds, but will still handle lighter or heavier rounds with more than acceptable downrange accuracy, and is chrome molly-coated for added durability. Upper is chambered for 5.56x45, so will easily handle either .223 or the hotter 5.56 depending on your preference. Lower is multi-cal marked, with pictograph safety selector symbols (think HK rifles). 

Will also include two USGI 30-round magazines to get you shooting sooner! Standard M-4 furniture, and can include a Rock River Arms carry-handle for an extra $50 if that's your sighting preference. Will consider partial trades, but only if they are of exceptional value because I'm really looking for more of a cash deal on this one. Thank you for your time, and don't hesitate to shoot me an offer.  This is likely the lowest priced new AR you will find on the site.

title: For Sale:  Transfer Services
postcontent:
Buying or Selling a gun Face to Face?

Do you want to make sure you are covered in the worst case scenario and everything is legal?

Gun Envy offers a transfer service where you can meet face to face here in Grove City.  If you wish to conclude the sale we can take the firearm into our possession, log it through our system and back out to the receiving party.  

As an FFL when we book it into our system the seller will prove their ID to us, then the receiving party will need to complete the 4473 form and pass the Instant Background Check before receiving the firearm.

Why would you want to do this?

As a seller you want to be sure that the buck does not stop at you if something bad happens with the firearm.  Being transferred to an FFL puts the firearm on the books and records definitively that you no longer posses it.

As the buyer you want to be sure of what you are getting.  Should this firearm end up having a record, you have followed a process that allows you to push it back to the dealer and we in turn can trace back to the seller.

All in all it allows both parties to be secure in the transaction for just $10 each.  Payment can be made at the time in Cash/Credit Card by one party or split between both.

Call us if you have any questions on REDACTED or Email us at REDACTED.

Gun Envy LLC is a licensed Federal Firearms Dealer in Grove City.

After 5 years of searching, I finally scored the 1911 I always wanted. So, up for sale goes my old friend here. It's a Kimber Series 1 classic stainless. The Series I pistols are fairly hard to find and are generally considered to be superior in quality control all around. There are a few very minor imperfections (not the picture of the front strap), but at a glance, this pistol is in almost new condition. Comes with box and one 7 round blued magazine. Price is $850 ftf in Norman. Remember, this is a Series I, NOT a Series II.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Trade for a Honda 250 and a Taurus 66?
postcontent:
I am looking to trade my Honda CH250cc Elite for a rifle in .308, 7.62x39 or a 9mm handgun preferrably with a decock feature.  I also will toss in a nice Taurus 66 in case the value of your firearm exceeds what I have.

Here is a description of the Honda: The Honda CH250 was an automatic transmission scooter capable of 70 mph (112kph) at around 70 mpg. A highly collectible scooter today!
The various common names stem from whichever region they were distributed. Elite: North America, Freeway: Japan, Spacy; rest of the world.
It has a pedal on the right side for the rear brake, and a hand grip on the right handlebar for the front disc brake. As an automatic there is no gear shift, but the brake pedal seems to incorporate a clutch for the automatic transmission. Electric starts reliably on the first try of the switch. The radiator fill-cap is located in the handy glove box. There is plenty of underseat luggage area, and some also have a cargo box on the rear rack which also adds lots of storage space as well as a nice backrest for the rear passenger. Perfect for the family outing and bringing home the groceries.
The engine delivers plenty of power, even for hill climbing at freeway speeds. Reports in that it tends to run wide on turns but otherwise handles like a regular motorcycle but with the advantage of stepping through and not having to through your leg over. The windscreen is reported as a little low for freeway cruising in wet weather, the rider needing to pull their head down (which of course leaves your pillion wide open to the inclement weather).
